Package: AddFonts
Title: Add Fonts from Several Providers to 'showtext'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Guillaume", "Noblet", , "gnoblet@zaclys.net", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Download and register fonts from several providers for use in R graphics 
    with the 'showtext' package. Currently supports Bunny Fonts (<https://fonts.bunny.net/>), 
    a privacy-focused alternative to Google Fonts. Functions are designed similar to 
    'font_add_google()' with extensible architecture for additional font providers.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE, packages = "roxytypes")
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Config/Needs/documentation: roxytypes
SystemRequirements: woff2 (>= 1.0.2): woff2-tools (rpm) or woff2 (deb)
Imports: 
    sysfonts,
    httr2,
    fs,
    rappdirs,
    cli
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    usethis,
    ggplot2,
    showtext
Config/testthat/edition: 3
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1.0)
URL: https://github.com/gnoblet/AddFonts, http://guillaume-noblet.com/AddFonts/
